{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877251545,"sessionID":"ses_28578733dffeSETOTYCQTCsJmH","part":{"id":"prt_d7a884c80001zcfflmDPniJRHg","messageID":"msg_d7a883ed4001ntyaEnRNFlOCMe","sessionID":"ses_28578733dffeSETOTYCQTCsJmH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-015\n2: title: PicoD 命令执行 API\n3: module: pkg/picod\n4: language: Go\n5: size: M\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API\n9: # Module: pkg/picod\n10: # Language: Go\n11: # Size: M\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: picod-command-execution-api\n21:   description: |\n22:     Implement the PicoD (Pico Daemon) command execution API that provides\n23:     a lightweight, sandboxed environment for running commands within agent\n24:     sessions. PicoD serves as the execution engine for the agentcube platform,\n25:     enabling secure command isolation, resource limiting, and output streaming\n26:     capabilities.\n27: \n28: # Scope\n29: scope:\n30:   in:\n31:     - PicoD command execution API definition and implementation\n32:     - Command request/response protocol design\n33:     - Sandbox lifecycle management (create, execute, destroy)\n34:     - Resource limiting (CPU, memory, I/O) integration\n35:     - Output streaming (stdout/stderr capture)\n36:     - Error handling and execution status reporting\n37:     - Security context and privilege isolation\n38:   out:\n39:     - Full sandbox orchestration (covered in AR-009)\n40:     - WebSocket real-time streaming (future enhancement)\n41:     - Multi-node distributed execution\n42:     - Custom runtime environments\n43: \n44: # Acceptance Criteria\n45: acceptance:\n46:   - Command execution API with structured request/response\n47:   - Synchronous and asynchronous execution modes\n48:   - Resource limit enforcement integration\n49:   - Output capture and streaming support\n50:   - Execution status tracking (pending, running, completed, failed)\n51:   - Timeout and cancellation support\n52:   - Proper error codes and message propagation\n53:   - Unit tests for core execution logic\n54:   - Integration tests with mock sandbox environment\n55: \n56: # References\n57: references:\n58:   - AR-009: 沙箱编排系统\n59:   - AR-012: 会话存储接口定义\n60: \n61: # Estimation\n62: estimation:\n63:   size: M\n64:   story_points: 5\n65:   days: 4\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-015\ntitle: PicoD 命令执行 API\nmodule: pkg/picod\nlanguage: Go\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API\n# Module: pkg/picod\n# Language: Go\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: picod-command-execution-api","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775877251520,"end":1775877251544}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877251547,"sessionID":"ses_28578733dffeSETOTYCQTCsJmH","part":{"id":"prt_d7a88536d001vjzNrsj5tKxEvo","messageID":"msg_d7a883ed4001ntyaEnRNFlOCMe","sessionID":"ses_28578733dffeSETOTYCQTCsJmH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n14: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n15: │  CommandExecutor  │  ExecutionManager  │  OutputBuffer  │\n16: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n17: │              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n18: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n19: │              Resource Limiter (Integration)              │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Key Interfaces\n24: \n25: #### CommandExecutor\n26: \n27: The primary interface for executing commands through PicoD.\n28: \n29: ```go\n30: type CommandExecutor interface {\n31:     Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n32:     ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n33:     GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n34:     Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n35:     StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n36: }\n37: ```\n38: \n39: #### ExecutionRequest\n40: \n41: Configuration for a command execution.\n42: \n43: ```go\n44: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n45:     Command     string\n46:     Args        []string\n47:     WorkingDir  string\n48:     Environment map[string]string\n49:     Timeout     time.Duration\n50:     ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n51:     SessionID   string\n52: }\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### ExecutionResult\n56: \n57: Result of a command execution.\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: type ExecutionResult struct {\n61:     ID         ExecutionID\n62:     Status     ExecutionStatus\n63:     ExitCode   int\n64:     Stdout     []byte\n65:     Stderr     []byte\n66:     StartedAt  time.Time\n67:     FinishedAt time.Time\n68:     Error      *ExecutionError\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ## Data Flow\n73: \n74: ### Synchronous Execution\n75: \n76: ```\n77: 1. Client calls Execute()\n78: 2. PicoD validates request and resource limits\n79: 3. Sandbox environment is prepared\n80: 4. Command is executed with monitoring\n81: 5. Output is captured\n82: 6. Result is returned to client\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ### Asynchronous Execution\n86: \n87: ```\n88: 1. Client calls ExecuteAsync()\n89: 2. Execution is queued with initial status \"pending\"\n90: 3. Background worker picks up execution\n91: 4. Status updates to \"running\"\n92: 5. Output is streamed to buffer\n93: 6. On completion, status updates to \"completed\" or \"failed\"\n94: 7. Client polls GetStatus() or receives callback\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ## Error Handling\n98: \n99: ### Error Types\n100: \n101: - `ErrInvalidRequest`: Malformed execution request\n102: - `ErrResourceExceeded`: Resource limits exceeded\n103: - `ErrTimeout`: Execution exceeded timeout\n104: - `ErrSandboxUnavailable`: Sandbox environment not available\n105: - `ErrExecutionFailed`: Command returned non-zero exit code\n106: - `ErrCancelled`: Execution was cancelled\n107: \n108: ### Status States\n109: \n110: ```\n111: pending → running → completed\n112:               ↓\n113:             failed\n114:               ↓\n115:            cancelled\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ## Security Considerations\n119: \n120: - Commands run in isolated sandbox environment\n121: - Resource limits enforced at sandbox level\n122: - No direct shell access\n123: - Environment variable filtering\n124: - Working directory restrictions\n125: \n126: ## Performance Considerations\n127: \n128: - Connection pooling to sandbox service\n129: - Output buffering with size limits\n130: - Concurrent execution limits\n131: - Timeout enforcement at multiple levels\n132: \n133: ## Open Questions\n134: \n135: 1. Maximum output size limits?\n136: 2. Real-time streaming protocol?\n137: 3. Multi-tenancy isolation model?\n138: 4. Execution queue prioritization?\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  CommandExecutor  │  ExecutionManager  │  OutputBuffer  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Resource Limiter (Integration)              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","time":{"start":1775877251525,"end":1775877251546}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877251550,"sessionID":"ses_28578733dffeSETOTYCQTCsJmH","part":{"id":"prt_d7a885a39001Q7rQuZ2WYvW3t6","messageID":"msg_d7a883ed4001ntyaEnRNFlOCMe","sessionID":"ses_28578733dffeSETOTYCQTCsJmH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD command execution API.\n6: \n7: ## Phase 1: API Design and Interface Definition\n8: \n9: - [ ] Define command execution request/response structures\n10: - [ ] Design PicoD client interface\n11: - [ ] Define execution options (timeout, resource limits, env vars)\n12: - [ ] Document error codes and status states\n13: \n14: ## Phase 2: Core Implementation\n15: \n16: - [ ] Implement CommandExecutor struct and methods\n17: - [ ] Implement synchronous execution flow\n18: - [ ] Implement asynchronous execution with status tracking\n19: - [ ] Add resource limit integration points\n20: \n21: ## Phase 3: Output Handling\n22: \n23: - [ ] Design output capture mechanism\n24: - [ ] Implement stdout/stderr collection\n25: - [ ] Add output streaming support (buffer-based)\n26: - [ ] Handle large output scenarios\n27: \n28: ## Phase 4: Error Handling and Status\n29: \n30: - [ ] Implement execution status lifecycle\n31: - [ ] Add timeout and cancellation support\n32: - [ ] Design error translation layer\n33: - [ ] Add execution result metadata\n34: \n35: ## Phase 5: Testing\n36: \n37: - [ ] Write unit tests for execution logic\n38: - [ ] Create mock sandbox for testing\n39: - [ ] Add integration tests\n40: - [ ] Performance and resource limit tests\n41: \n42: ## Dependencies\n43: \n44: - AR-009: Sandbox orchestration system (for integration)\n45: - AR-012: Session storage interface (for status persistence)\n46: \n47: ## Estimated Timeline\n48: \n49: - Phase 1: 1 day\n50: - Phase 2: 1.5 days\n51: - Phase 3: 1 day\n52: - Phase 4: 0.5 day\n53: - Phase 5: 1 day\n54: \n55: Total: 4-5 days\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Implementation Plan\n\n## Overview\n\nThis plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD command execution API.\n\n## Phase 1: API Design and Interface Definition\n\n- [ ] Define command execution request/response structures\n- [ ] Design PicoD client interface\n- [ ] Define execution options (timeout, resource limits, env vars)\n- [ ] Document error codes and status states\n\n## Phase 2: Core Implementation\n\n- [ ] Implement CommandExecutor struct and methods\n- [ ] Implement synchronous execution flow\n- [ ] Implement asynchronous execution with status tracking\n- [ ] Add resource limit integration points\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md","time":{"start":1775877251527,"end":1775877251548}}}}
