tatus persistence |\n463: | AR-013: Redis Implementation | Store backend option |\n464: | AR-014: Valkey Implementation | Store backend option |\n465: | `github.com/google/uuid` | ExecutionID generation |\n466: | `pkg/common/types` | Shared types |\n467: \n468: ---\n469: \n470: ## Design Notes\n471: \n472: - **Execution ID format:** `[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+`, 8-64 characters\n473: - **State machine:** pending → running → completed | failed | cancelled\n474: - **Terminal states:** completed, failed, cancelled (immutable)\n475: - **Output buffering:** Circular buffer with configurable size\n476: - **Concurrency:** Semaphore-based limit enforcement\n477: - **Timeout:** Context-based with cancellation propagation\n478: - **Sandbox integration:** Via AR-009 interface\n479: - **Store integration:** Via AR-012 interface\n480: - **Environment config:** PICOD_* variables\n\n(End of file - total 480 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API (PicoD Command Execution API)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-015 implements the PicoD command execution API providing synchronous and asynchronous command execution in sandbox environments. The API supports resource constraints, output streaming, execution cancellation, and persistent status tracking.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Type Definitions and Interfaces\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775877260621,"end":1775877260642}}}}
